SIMPLE: drawknife
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drawknife
<hw>Draw"knife`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A woodworker`s and
joiner's tool having a blade with a handle at each end, used to shave
off surfaces, by drawing it toward one; a shave; -- called also
<altname>drawshave</altname>, and <altname>drawing
shave</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Carp.)</fld> <def>A tool used for the purpose of
making an incision along the path a saw is to follow, to prevent it from
tearing the surface of the wood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawing-room</ent>⟦br⟧

